    Function.Injective (toDiffeologicalSpace : GroupDiffeology G → DiffeologicalSpace G) :=
  fun f g h ↦ by cases f; cases g; congr
```

This lemma is showing that the map from group diffeologies to diffeological spaces is injective. This is straightforward because a group diffeology must contain at least the identity map, and different group diffeologies will result in different diffeological spaces.

