```tactics
@[to_additive]
theorem toDiffeologicalSpace_injective :
    Function.Injective (toDiffeologicalSpace : GroupDiffeology G → DiffeologicalSpace G) :=
  fun f g h ↦ by cases f; cases g; congr
```

This proves that the map `toDiffeologicalSpace` is injective. This is true because two different group diffeologies cannot have the same underlying diffeology.

```tactics
@[to_additive (attr := ext)]
theorem ext' {d₁ d₂ : GroupDiffeology G} (h : d₁.1 = d₂.1) : d₁ = d₂ :=
  toDiffeologicalSpace_injective h
```

This provides an extensionality principle for group diffeologies. If two group diffeologies have the same underlying diffeology, then they are the same group diffeology.

